<p><strong>SourceWork Academic Writing from Sources, 2nd Edition: A Comprehensive Guide</strong></p>
<p><strong>What is SourceWork Academic Writing from Sources, 2nd Edition?</strong></p>
<p>SourceWork Academic Writing from Sources, 2nd Edition is a comprehensive reference guide designed to assist students in effectively using and incorporating sources into their academic writing. It provides clear and concise guidance on the principles and practices of academic source use, including proper citation and avoidance of plagiarism.</p>
<p><strong>What are the Key Features of SourceWork?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Step-by-Step Instructions:</strong> SourceWork offers a systematic approach to academic writing, guiding students through each stage of the research and writing process.</li>
<li><strong>Real-World Examples:</strong> The book includes numerous real-world examples and student writing samples to illustrate the concepts and techniques being taught.</li>
<li><strong>Comprehensive Coverage:</strong> SourceWork covers a wide range of topics, including finding and evaluating sources, summarizing and paraphrasing, quoting and citing, and avoiding plagiarism.</li>
<li><strong>Citation Guides:</strong> The book provides detailed citation guides for all major citation styles, ensuring that students can cite their sources accurately and consistently.</li>
<li><strong>Interactive Exercises:</strong> SourceWork features interactive exercises and activities that help students apply the principles they have learned.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Who is SourceWork for?</strong></p>
<p>SourceWork Academic Writing from Sources, 2nd Edition is a valuable resource for undergraduate and graduate students in all academic disciplines. It is particularly beneficial for students who are new to academic writing or who need to improve their source integration skills.</p>
<p><strong>Can I Find SourceWork Online?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, SourceWork Academic Writing from Sources, 2nd Edition is available as an e-book or a PDF download. You can purchase the e-book from online retailers such as Amazon or Barnes &amp; Noble. To obtain a PDF copy, you may need to contact your university library or a commercial document delivery service.</p>